element.name: Mary Love's quest for happpiness. by Mary Love, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)
element.description: It'll make Mary Love's day if you log this cache.
element.long-description: The cache is located in the not so pretty and not so manicured end of Santry Woods. The park may be accessed from the Coolock Lane/Swords Raod junction or from the other end; turning off at the Topaz filling station on the Ballymun Road and taking the next left.

ul.li:
2010-05-22T19:00:00Z : Found it by photomaniac99
Last minute find! Nearly gave up but not abra123cadabra. Just made it back to the car before the gates of the park where closed.

2010-05-22T19:00:00Z : Found it by abra123cadabra
With limited time at hand (park closes at 8pm in May) we almost gave up when I spotted the cache. It was where we thought it would be, just a few centimetres away. GPSr didn't really know where GZ should be but the likely hiding place was quickly identified. It definitely made our day.

2010-05-19T19:00:00Z : Found it by evosheas
There you go Mary, logged by an Aussie. Cheers.
